Nike stores in South Africa were all open on Friday, the company said, after some were closed following a backlash over racist comments by a man said to have links to the United States sportswear company. Some stores were closed on Wednesday after the comments, in a video posted online, caused a public outcry. Nike was not mentioned in the video but local online news service said the man in the video was married to a merchandising director at Nike. Nike said Adam Catzavelos was not an employee of the company. Related video click below:  